<item>
            <title>[LU-2209] warnings due to installed lustre rc scripts in SLES11 SP2</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2209</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When doing package updates in SLES11 SP2 I see the following warnings, apparently due to installed lustre rc scripts:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;insserv: warning: script &apos;lnet&apos; missing LSB tags and overrides&lt;br/&gt;
insserv: Default-Start undefined, assuming default start runlevel(s) for script `lnet&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
insserv: warning: script &apos;lustre&apos; missing LSB tags and overrides&lt;br/&gt;
insserv: Default-Start undefined, assuming default start runlevel(s) for script `lustre&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this doesn&apos;t look at all fatal, it suggests some required header info is missing from lustre supplied rc scripts.  This should probably be cleaned up by adding headers that SLES likes/requires.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>SLES 11 SP2 client</environment>
